Class Mood

    java.io.Serializable

    public class Mood
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This is the Mood model class for the Moody application. It contains the data that is displayed in a user's posted mood.

      • Mood

        public Mood(java.lang.String feeling,
            java.lang.String username,
            java.lang.String moodMessage,
            double latitude,
            double longitude,
            android.graphics.Bitmap image,
            java.lang.String socialSituation,
            java.util.Date date,
            java.lang.String displayLocation)
        Constructor for the mood object. Takes in a mandatory feeling and username, and "optional" parameters such as location, imageID, mood message, and social situation. "Optional" parameters means that objects can be passed in as null.
        Parameters:
        feeling - The associated feeling of a mood (happiness, confusion, etc.)
        username - The user's username
        moodMessage - The textual explanation for a user's mood
        latitude - The user's pinned location (Will be null in part 4, as it's not yet implemented)
        longitude -
        socialSituation - The user's selected socialSituation (alone, with a crowd, etc.)

        public android.graphics.Bitmap decodeImage()

        Returns:

      • encodeImage

        public java.lang.String encodeImage(android.graphics.Bitmap moodImage)
        This method encodes and compresses a user's supplied bitmap image for appropriate storage on the application's server. Images stored on the server are all under 65536 bytes.
        Logic for compression of the image is from:
        link: http://blog.csdn.net/harryweasley/article/details/51955467
        Author: Harry Weasley
        Taken by: Xin Huang 2017/03/11
        Logic for encoding of image string was based upon:
        link: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/12796579/how-to-send-image-bitmap-to-server-in-android-with-multipart-form-data-json
        Author: Carnal
        Taken by: Michael Simion 2017/03/10
        Parameters:
        moodImage - The user's supplied image for his or her mood
        Returns:
        encodedImage The encodedImage string that will be stored within the object on the server
